description:
The D-Link Network Assistant (DNA) is a program that allows administrators to quickly discover all D-Link
smart switches and D-Link Discover Protocol (DDP) supported devices that are in the same subnet as the
DNA. It also collects traps and log messages, and provides quick access to basic configuration of the switch.
This tool is only for computers running 32/64-bit Windows 7/Vista/XP/2000.
summary:
The D-Link Network Assistant (DNA) is a program that allows administrators to quickly configure all D-Link
smart switches
author: D-Link Systems,  Inc.
